wikipedia_page.main: Nathaniel Pilch (born 4 September 1793 in Brisley, Norfolk; died 1881 in Erpingham, Norfolk) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Norfolk who was active from 1820 to 1836. He was the elder brother of Fuller Pilch. Pilch is recorded in six matches, totalling 173 runs with a highest score of 52, holding 6 catches and taking 3 wickets.
